"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(*)\nFROM badges\nJOIN users ON badges.UserId = users.Id\nWHERE users.DisplayName = 'csgillespie' AND YEAR(badges.Date) = 2011;\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of badges obtained by the user with the display name \"csgillespie\" in the year 2011. It joins the `badges` table with the `users` table using the foreign key relationship `badges.UserId = users.Id` and filters the results based on the display name and the year of the badge acquisition date."